text: Manuel Quintas de Almeida (1957 – 26 December 2006) was a lieutenant in the military of São Tomé and Príncipe. He led a coup against the democratically elected government of President Miguel Trovoada on 15 August 1995. He died on 26 December 2006, aged 52."Morreu Manuel Quintas de Almeida" , Jornal de São Tomé e Príncipe, 28 December 2006. ==References== Category:Heads of state of São Tomé and Príncipe Category:1957 births Category:2006 deaths
